{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"706d9c72-3383-4406-83d9-03df3f99a818","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** with .NET 9. Here's the recommended modern pattern:\n\n- **Constructor** — for sync init + `TestContext` injection\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — for async init (supports `async Task`)\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous setup here\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- MSTest v3 supports **constructor injection** of `TestContext` — no need for the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property.\n- The constructor runs first (sync), then `[TestInitialize]` runs (can be `async Task`).\n- There's also `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` (both support async) for one-time per-class setup.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df6fe2fc-9581-4bad-886a-05d1c48cc2ae","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection or the `TestContext` property. In MSTest 3.x, you can inject `TestContext` via constructor.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method or constructor.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an async method (MSTest 3.x supports async `[TestInitialize]`).\n\nLet me provide a clear, modern recommendation.\n\nIn MSTest 3.x:\n\n\n- `TestContext` can be injected through the constructor or via a property\n- The constructor handles synchronous setup while `[TestInitialize]` can be async\n- I'm showing the modern pattern with constructor injection and async initialization...","outputTokens":707,"requestId":"340D:B22B0:CFBA7F:F1DDB0:69F403BD"},"id":"1b10f2e8-ed92-440c-9058-1cb1016865bb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:37:15.054Z","parentId":"eca3511f-9930-4f18-b85e-c3cba3653bf2"}
